# Repair step instructions
rmc-hardpoint-repair-armor-compromised-1 = Tighten the armor fasteners and clamp the plate into alignment.
rmc-hardpoint-repair-armor-compromised-2 = Weld and patch the breached armor seams.
rmc-hardpoint-repair-feed-jam-1 = Open the feed cover and clear bent belt links.
rmc-hardpoint-repair-feed-jam-2 = Cycle the feed actuator with a multitool.
rmc-hardpoint-repair-runaway-trigger-1 = Open the trigger housing and isolate the worn sear linkage.
rmc-hardpoint-repair-runaway-trigger-2 = Reset the fire-control relay with a multitool.
rmc-hardpoint-repair-runaway-trigger-3 = Re-seat and tighten the trigger linkage.
rmc-hardpoint-repair-turret-traverse-1 = Tighten and re-index the traverse ring.
rmc-hardpoint-repair-turret-traverse-2 = Jack the turret bearing clear and re-seat the ring.
rmc-hardpoint-repair-engine-misfire-1 = Open the engine access panel.
rmc-hardpoint-repair-engine-misfire-2 = Pulse the ignition control circuit with a multitool.
rmc-hardpoint-repair-engine-misfire-3 = Tighten the engine mounts after the circuit stabilizes.
rmc-hardpoint-repair-transmission-slip-1 = Lift and re-seat the drivetrain with a maintenance jack.
rmc-hardpoint-repair-transmission-slip-2 = Tighten the transmission housing bolts.
rmc-hardpoint-repair-warped-frame-1 = Jack the frame and relieve pressure from the warped section.
rmc-hardpoint-repair-warped-frame-2 = Heat and straighten the warped frame members with a welder.
rmc-hardpoint-repair-warped-frame-3 = Re-torque the frame braces.
rmc-hardpoint-repair-damaged-mount-1 = Jack the hardpoint clear of the damaged mount.
rmc-hardpoint-repair-damaged-mount-2 = Re-seat and tighten the mount locking hardware.
rmc-hardpoint-repair-tire-blowout-1 = Pry the shredded tire casing clear of the rim.
rmc-hardpoint-repair-tire-blowout-2 = Jack the hub up and seat a replacement wheel assembly.
rmc-hardpoint-repair-tire-blowout-3 = Torque the wheel lugs down in sequence.
rmc-hardpoint-repair-thrown-tread-1 = Jack the running gear up and take tension off the tread.
rmc-hardpoint-repair-thrown-tread-2 = Pry the thrown tread links back onto the road wheels.
rmc-hardpoint-repair-thrown-tread-3 = Lock the tensioner and torque the tread pins.
rmc-hardpoint-repair-engine-overheat-1 = Open the engine shroud and vent trapped heat.
rmc-hardpoint-repair-engine-overheat-2 = Pry the warped fan guard away from the radiator.
rmc-hardpoint-repair-engine-overheat-3 = Pulse the coolant pump controller until flow stabilizes.
rmc-hardpoint-repair-electrical-short-1 = Cut away the burned wiring from the hardpoint harness.
rmc-hardpoint-repair-electrical-short-2 = Trace and reset the control circuit with a multitool.
rmc-hardpoint-repair-electrical-short-3 = Close the access panel and secure the replacement harness.
rmc-hardpoint-repair-fuel-leak-1 = Open the fuel service panel and isolate the ruptured line.
rmc-hardpoint-repair-fuel-leak-2 = Patch the leaking fuel line.
rmc-hardpoint-repair-fuel-leak-3 = Tighten the fuel line coupling.
